---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import DocsSidebar from "../../components/DocsSidebar.astro";
---
<Layout title="MCP server · flipagent docs">
	<div class="cmw cmw-bordered">
		<div class="docs-shell">
			<DocsSidebar />
			<article class="docs-content">
				<h1>MCP server</h1>
				<p class="lead">flipagent-mcp is a Model Context Protocol server that exposes the full reseller API as MCP tools. Works with any compatible AI client: Claude Desktop, Cursor, Cline, Zed, Windsurf.</p>

				<h2>Install</h2>
				<p>The MCP server is published on npm and runs through <code>npx</code>, so no global install is needed. The fastest path is the CLI:</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`npx -y flipagent-cli init --mcp`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>It auto-detects every supported client and writes the config in one go.</p>

				<h2>Claude Desktop (manual)</h2>
				<p>Edit <code>~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json</code>:</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": {
    "flipagent": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "flipagent-mcp"],
      "env": { "FLIPAGENT_API_KEY": "fa_free_xxx" }
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>Restart Claude. The tools below show up in any chat.</p>

				<h2>Cursor / Cline / Zed / Windsurf</h2>
				<p>Same JSON, different file:</p>
				<table class="api">
					<thead><tr><th>Client</th><th>Config file</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td>Cursor</td><td><code>.cursor/mcp.json</code> (in workspace)</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Cline</td><td><code>~/.cline/mcp.json</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td>Zed</td><td>Settings → MCP servers</td></tr>
						<tr><td>Windsurf</td><td>Settings → Cascade → MCP servers</td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>

				<h2>Tools exposed</h2>
				<table class="api">
					<thead><tr><th>Tool</th><th>Backed by</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Discovery</strong></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_search</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/buy/browse/item_summary/search</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_item_detail</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/buy/browse/item/&#123;itemId&#125;</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_sold_search</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/buy/marketplace_insights/item_sales/search</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_taxonomy_default_id</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/commerce/taxonomy/get_default_category_tree_id</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_taxonomy_suggest</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/commerce/taxonomy/category_tree/&#123;id&#125;/get_category_suggestions</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_taxonomy_aspects</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/commerce/taxonomy/category_tree/&#123;id&#125;/get_item_aspects_for_category</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Decisions</strong></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>evaluate_listing</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/evaluate</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>evaluate_signals</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/evaluate/signals</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>research_summary</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/research/summary</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>match_pool</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/match</code> &mdash; hosted or delegate, see below</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_match_trace</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/traces/match</code> &mdash; opt-out telemetry, see below</td></tr>
						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Overnight</strong></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>discover_deals</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/discover</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>draft_listing</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/draft</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>reprice_listing</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/reprice</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Operations</strong></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ship_quote</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/ship/quote</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ship_providers</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/ship/providers</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td colspan="2"><strong>Sell-side</strong> (eBay OAuth required via <code>/v1/connect/ebay</code>)</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>flipagent_connect_status</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/connect/ebay/status</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_create_inventory_item</code></td><td><code>PUT /v1/sell/inventory/inventory_item/&#123;sku&#125;</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_create_offer</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/sell/inventory/offer</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_publish_offer</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/sell/inventory/offer/&#123;offerId&#125;/publish</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_list_orders</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/sell/fulfillment/order</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_mark_shipped</code></td><td><code>POST /v1/sell/fulfillment/order/&#123;orderId&#125;/shipping_fulfillment</code></td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>ebay_list_payouts</code></td><td><code>GET /v1/sell/finances/payout</code></td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>

				<h2 id="hosted-vs-delegate">Hosted vs delegate</h2>
				<p><code>match_pool</code> is the only tool that runs an LLM. It supports two execution modes — pick whichever fits your host agent.</p>
				<table class="api">
					<thead><tr><th>Mode</th><th>Where the LLM runs</th><th>Best for</th></tr></thead>
					<tbody>
						<tr><td><code>hosted</code> (default)</td><td>flipagent backend &mdash; we eat the cost</td><td>weak-host agents, scripts, cron, deterministic batched runs</td></tr>
						<tr><td><code>delegate</code></td><td>your host agent's own LLM</td><td>strong agents already paying for inference (Claude Code, Cursor) &mdash; saves the round-trip</td></tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
				<p>Switch via <code>options.mode</code>:</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`await match_pool({
  candidate,
  pool: sold.itemSales,
  options: { mode: "delegate" }
});
// → { mode: "delegate", system, user, itemIds, outputSchema, traceId }`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>In delegate mode the server returns a ready-to-run prompt + JSON schema. Your host LLM reasons over it, returns <code>[&#123;i, bucket, reason&#125;]</code> per pool item, and you materialise the two-bucket <code>MatchResponse</code> locally.</p>

				<h2 id="telemetry">Telemetry &amp; opt-out</h2>
				<p><code>flipagent_match_trace</code> is the only telemetry path. After delegate-mode <code>match_pool</code>, the host can post its decisions back so flipagent's calibration data stays current as host LLMs drift.</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Opt-out, not opt-in.</strong> Runs by default.</li>
					<li><strong>Anonymous.</strong> We store the trace id we issued, the per-item decisions, and a SHA-256 prefix of your API key for rate-limit accounting. No account link.</li>
					<li><strong>Bounded.</strong> Only triggers after delegate-mode <code>match_pool</code>. Hosted runs and read-only tools never produce traces.</li>
				</ul>
				<p>Disable with an environment variable in your MCP client config (matches the OSS norm — <code>HOMEBREW_NO_ANALYTICS</code>, <code>NEXT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED</code>, <code>ASTRO_TELEMETRY_DISABLED</code>):</p>
				<div class="code"><pre><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": {
    "flipagent": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "flipagent-mcp"],
      "env": {
        "FLIPAGENT_API_KEY": "fa_free_xxx",
        "FLIPAGENT_TELEMETRY": "0"
      }
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre></div>
				<p>Accepted off-values: <code>0</code>, <code>off</code>, <code>false</code>, <code>no</code>, <code>disabled</code>. When disabled, <code>flipagent_match_trace</code> short-circuits with <code>&#123; skipped: "telemetry_disabled" &#125;</code> and never makes a network call.</p>

				<h2>Compose your own logic</h2>
				<p>Tools are typed and orthogonal. Agents can chain <code>ebay_search</code> → <code>ebay_sold_search</code> → <code>match_pool</code> → <code>discover_deals</code> → <code>ship_quote</code> to assemble end-to-end reselling workflows. See the <a href="/docs/api/">API reference</a> for request shapes.</p>
			</article>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>
